{
  "doc_id": "48921",
  "text": "The CVS model used to describe the cardiovascular system was first described by Smith et al [CITATION_1] and has already been validated in silico and in several animal model studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . It is a lumped parameter model consisting of six elastic chambers, the left ventricle (lv), the right (rv) ventricle, the vena cava (vc), the aorta (ao), the pulmonary artery (pa) and the pulmonary veins (pu), linked by vessels presenting a resistance to the blood flow. The diagram of this model is presented in Figure 1 .",
